GET BACK OUT THERE,

13:28.474 --> 13:30.559
AND MAKE THE BIGGEST DECISION
OF MY LIFE.

13:30.643 --> 13:34.522
- JOY? CHOOSE A GOOD ONE.
YOU DESERVE IT.

13:34.605 --> 13:38.359
- OKAY, I'M WAITING.
WHERE'S THE INSULT?

13:38.442 --> 13:40.903
I'VE GOT NO BOOBS, I'M OLD,
I'M SKANKY...

13:40.986 --> 13:43.822
- I'M SAVING THOSE
FOR YOUR WEDDING TOAST.

13:48.827 --> 13:51.539
- BOB, YOU'RE A TERRIFIC GUY.
BUT, WE'VE NEVER EVEN BEEN

13:51.622 --> 13:54.416
ON A DATE.
MARRIAGE SEEMS QUITE THE LEAP.

13:54.500 --> 13:58.420
- FINE, FORGET ME.
FOCUS ON YOUR OTHER TWO SUITORS.

13:58.504 --> 14:00.047
LET'S FACE IT,
BOTH MITCH AND SIMON

14:00.130 --> 14:02.299
ARE GONNA LOSE THEIR LOOKS.
WHERE AS I?

14:02.383 --> 14:05.719
WILL LOOK LIKE THIS FOREVER.

14:05.803 --> 14:07.888
WELL, AS LONG AS
SHOPPERS DRUG MART CONTINUES

14:07.972 --> 14:11.892
TO MAKE "APRICOT KISS FOAM-IN
HAIR COLOR, FOR MEN."

14:11.976 --> 14:15.563
- STOP MAKING ME LAUGH.
- WHY, JOY? YOU LOVE TO LAUGH.

14:15.646 --> 14:19.108
I COULD GUARANTEE YOU
A LIFETIME OF LAUGHTER.

14:19.191 --> 14:22.820
JOY, I'VE BEEN IN LOVE WITH YOU
FROM THE FIRST MOMENT I MET YOU.

14:22.903 --> 14:25.948
- BUT, WHAT ABOUT
YOUR GIRLFRIEND IN CANADA?

14:26.031 --> 14:28.075
ARE YOU SURE THAT'S OVER?

14:28.158 --> 14:29.743
- HER LAST WORDS TO ME WERE,

14:29.827 --> 14:33.455
"GET OUT OF HERE, YOU BIG DICK."

14:33.539 --> 14:34.915
- I'M SORRY.

14:34.999 --> 14:38.002
- FOCUS ON THE LAST TWO WORDS,
JOY.

14:38.085 --> 14:41.755
- [laughs]

14:41.839 --> 14:44.842
- I LOVE JOY SO MUCH.
SHE SHOULD BE WITH ME.

14:44.925 --> 14:46.468
IT'S AS PLAIN THE NOSE ON MY--

14:46.552 --> 14:49.471
HOLY CRAP!

14:49.555 --> 14:52.641
- YOU OBVIOUSLY RECOGNIZE ME
FROM <i> CLEVELAND MAGAZINE.</i>

14:52.725 --> 14:56.520
- YEAH, THAT'S IT.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.608
- WHAT DO I DO IF JOY DOESN'T
PICK ME?

15:00.691 --> 15:02.276
I'LL BE LOST,
I'LL BE DEVASTATED,

15:02.359 --> 15:04.278
I--I WON'T BE ABLE TO GO ON.

15:04.361 --> 15:07.156
- LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING.
WERE YOU ALWAYS A MAN?

15:10.534 --> 15:12.620
- YOU COULD ALWAYS
MAKE ME SMILE.

15:12.703 --> 15:15.289
- OH, ELKA.
IF ONLY YOU WERE A MAN.

15:15.372 --> 15:18.459
- I WAS JUST ABOUT TO SAY
THE SAME THING.

15:21.587 --> 15:25.799
- WHAT THE HELL IS GOING ON,
HERE?

15:25.883 --> 15:29.637
- JOY, YOU MEAN THE WORLD TO ME.
WE'RE SOUL MATES.

15:29.720 --> 15:33.349
EVEN AFTER I LOST 300 POUNDS,
I WOULD LOOK AT MYSELF

15:33.432 --> 15:35.976
IN THE MIRROR,
AND I WOULD SEE A FAT GUY.

15:36.060 --> 15:38.896
BUT YOUR LOVE HAS GIVEN ME
THE CONFIDENCE TO SEE MYSELF

15:38.979 --> 15:40.648
FOR WHO I TRULY AM...

15:40.731 --> 15:42.733
A VERY HANDSOME MAN.

15:42.816 --> 15:44.026
- MITCH.

15:44.109 --> 15:48.030
- I'M VERY HANDSOME, JOY.

15:48.113 --> 15:50.658
BORDERLINE PRETTY.

15:52.785 --> 15:55.204
- YOU REALLY ARE.
- AND YOU ARE...

15:55.287 --> 15:59.041
A LITTLE SHALLOW, RIGHT?
- MORE THAN A LITTLE.

15:59.124 --> 16:01.669
- THEN PICTURE WAKING UP
FOR THE NEXT 50 YEARS

16:01.752 --> 16:05.089
NEXT TO SIMON, OR BOB,
OR, WAKING UP...

16:05.172 --> 16:09.385
NEXT TO THIS.

16:09.468 --> 16:11.178
- YOU MAKE A LOT OF SENSE,
MITCH.

16:11.261 --> 16:14.515
A LOT OF SENSE.

16:14.598 --> 16:18.060
- SO, MARCY. BRIAN AND I HAVE
BEEN, UM, TALKING,

16:18.143 --> 16:19.853
AND HE HAS SOMETHING THAT
HE WOULD LIKE TO SAY TO YOU.

16:19.937 --> 16:20.938
BRIAN?

16:21.021 --> 16:24.525
- YES. MARCY, UH, I, YOU SEE--

16:24.608 --> 16:26.777
- SORRY TO INTERRUPT. MELANIE?
- WHAT?

16:26.860 --> 16:28.737
- I NEED YOUR HELP TO WIN JOY.
ANYTHING THAT WILL MAKE HER

16:28.821 --> 16:30.239
WANT ME OVER ALL OTHER MEN.

16:30.322 --> 16:32.241
- MAYBE I CAN HELP.
BY HAVING SEX WITH ME,

16:32.324 --> 16:33.283
YOU'LL BECOME A BETTER LOVER.

16:33.367 --> 16:36.787
-YOU HAVE MY ATTENTION.

16:36.870 --> 16:40.082
- NO, I--I--I DON'T WANT YOU
HAVING SEX WITH ANYBODY BUT ME.

16:40.165 --> 16:43.460
- I'M FLATTERED, BUT--

16:43.544 --> 16:46.088
- NOT YOU, HER.

16:46.171 --> 16:48.424
HE'S IN LOVE WITH HER.

16:48.507 --> 16:51.427
- IS THIS TRUE?
- YES, MARCY.

16:51.510 --> 16:54.221
- SO, WHEN I TAUGHT YOU TO
CALL OUT MELANIE'S NAME,

16:54.304 --> 16:56.098
YOU--YOU ACTUALLY WANTED
TO CALL OUT MINE?

16:56.181 --> 16:58.934
- [laughing] YES.
NO, I ONLY THOUGHT OF MELANIE

16:59.017 --> 17:01.437
WHEN I NEEDED TO DISTRACT MYSELF
TO MAKE IT LAST LONGER.

17:01.520 --> 17:04.940
- OH!

17:05.022 --> 17:07.401
- SOMETIMES I'D THINK OF
HER RADIO SHOW, AND...

17:07.483 --> 17:10.738
I COULD LAST ALL NIGHT.

17:10.820 --> 17:14.241
- I'M GONNA NEED TAPE
OF YOUR SHOW.

17:14.324 --> 17:17.077
- SO, TREVOR, YOU'RE A MODEL.
HOW DO GOOD-LOOKING GUYS,

17:17.161 --> 17:19.788
LIKE US, WIN A WOMAN?

17:19.872 --> 17:23.416
- IT'S NOT ABOUT THE LOOKS.
IF YOU REALLY WANNA CAPTURE

17:23.500 --> 17:25.669
JOY'S HEART,
DO SOMETHING HUMANITARIAN.

17:25.752 --> 17:28.797
WOMEN LOVE THAT.
- DO THEY?

17:28.881 --> 17:32.509
- WELL, YEAH. AND YOU ONLY KNOW
ABOUT THE EAR AND THE NOSE.

17:32.593 --> 17:34.887
YOU WON'T BELIEVE WHAT I GOT

17:34.970 --> 17:37.306
GROWING ON MY BACK.

17:37.389 --> 17:40.350
YOU'LL SEE.

17:40.434 --> 17:42.686
- WILL IT SEE ME?

17:42.770 --> 17:45.689
TELL ME NOW.

17:45.773 --> 17:48.817
- YOU DID A GOOD THING, MELANIE.
- YEAH, I DID, DIDN'T I?

17:48.901 --> 17:51.945
- WHY ARE WE STILL SITTING HERE?

17:52.029 --> 17:54.156
AND WHERE'S MITCH GOING?
IT'S NOT HIS TURN.

17:54.239 --> 17:57.367
- CAN I GET YOU ANOTHER DRINK?

17:57.451 --> 17:59.787
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

18:03.749 --> 18:07.669
- JOY. WHEN I LOOK AT YOU,
I SEE THE TEENAGE GIRL

18:07.753 --> 18:11.131
I FELL IN LOVE WITH. AND THAT'S
WHO I'M ALWAYS GONNA SEE.

18:11.215 --> 18:14.176
- REALLY?

18:16.929 --> 18:18.847
- DANCING?

18:18.931 --> 18:22.184
I DIDN'T KNOW
THERE'D BE A DANCING PORTION.

18:22.267 --> 18:26.105
- LET GO OF HER.
- NO, YOU LET GO OF HER.

18:26.188 --> 18:27.523
- SHE'S MINE.
- SHE'S MINE!

18:27.606 --> 18:29.233
- STOP IT! ALL OF YOU!

18:34.196 --> 18:35.739
- OH MY GOD.

18:41.912 --> 18:45.207
- THIS HAS BEEN QUITE A JOURNEY
FOR YOU, JOY.

18:45.290 --> 18:49.044
HAVE YOU MADE YOUR DECISION?
- I THINK I HAVE.

18:49.127 --> 18:50.963
I CHOOSE--

18:51.046 --> 18:54.508
I CHOOSE...

18:54.591 --> 18:57.010
WAIT A MINUTE,

18:57.094 --> 18:58.554
YOU'RE NOT CHRIS HARRISON.

18:58.637 --> 19:00.514
- YOU'VE HAD A BAD BUMP,
SWEETIE.

19:00.597 --> 19:03.892
YOU NEED TO LIE
QUIET FOR A WHILE.

19:03.976 --> 19:07.187
- I FEEL TERRIBLE.
I'VE NEVER HIT A WOMAN BEFORE.

19:07.271 --> 19:10.566
- ME EITHER...
EXCEPT THE TIME AN ELBOW

19:10.649 --> 19:14.570
GOT AWAY FROM ME IN ZUMBA CLASS.

19:14.653 --> 19:15.904
- CHEER UP, SIMON.

19:15.988 --> 19:18.448
IF JOY DOESN'T PICK YOU...

19:18.532 --> 19:21.869
I'M RIGHT HERE.

19:21.952 --> 19:23.871
- YOU KNOW BOB, I'VE ALWAYS
THOUGHT YOU WERE KINDA CUTE.

19:23.954 --> 19:25.080
I'D GO OUT WITH YOU.

19:25.163 --> 19:27.624
- KEEP IT IN YOUR PANTS,
MELANIE.

19:27.708 --> 19:29.877
I'M IN LOVE WITH JOY.

19:29.960 --> 19:33.755
- WHAT A NICE NIGHT IT'S BEEN.

19:33.839 --> 19:36.800
- IT WAS GREAT TO SEE STAN
AGAIN, BUT...

19:36.884 --> 19:38.927
I REALLY HAD A FEELING
I WAS GONNA

19:39.011 --> 19:40.721
MEET A SPECIAL MAN TONIGHT.

19:43.891 --> 19:45.601
- ELKA?

19:45.684 --> 19:49.271
- MAX! WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

19:49.354 --> 19:50.939
- I THOUGHT I WAS
HAVING HEART TROUBLE.

19:51.023 --> 19:53.942
BUT IT WAS NOTHING.
ALTHOUGH, NOW,

19:54.026 --> 19:56.320
IT'S STARTING TO RACE AGAIN.

19:56.403 --> 19:58.614
- [laughs] IS IT?

19:58.697 --> 20:02.451
- YOU KNOW, I'M JUST VISITING
FROM FLORIDA,

20:02.534 --> 20:05.454
I'M NOT STAYING VERY LONG, BUT,
UH, WOULD YOU, UH--

20:05.537 --> 20:08.582
- YES!
- AND MAYBE TOMORROW?

20:08.665 --> 20:11.919
- YES.
- AND THERE WAS SOMETHING ELSE

20:12.002 --> 20:14.338
I WANTED TO ASK YOU...UH...

20:14.421 --> 20:17.090
- WHEN YOU REMEMBER IT, YES.

20:19.551 --> 20:23.180
- OKAY, SHE'S DOING FINE.
SHE JUST NEEDS TO REST.

20:23.263 --> 20:24.514
- DID SHE SAY ANYTHING ABOUT
WHICH MAN

20:24.598 --> 20:26.016
SHE WAS GOING TO MARRY?

20:26.099 --> 20:28.644
- SHE'S IN NO CONDITION TO BE
MAKING LIFE DECISIONS.

20:28.727 --> 20:32.230
- THEN, I...GUESS EVERYONE
IS JUST GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.

